usinessinsider.com%2Fbond-market-selloff-highest-treasury-yield-2007-disruption-war-inflation-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20highest%2030-year%20Treasury%20yield%20in%20decades%20is%20disrupting%20best-laid%20plans%20for%20stock%20bulls%20and%20President%20Trump.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jciolli%40businessinsider.com%20(Joe%20Ciolli)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20entrepreneur%20who%20made%20Oprah's%20'Favorite%20Things'%20explains%20how%20to%20create%20a%20product%20that%20people%20are%20obsessed%20with%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tal%20Moore%2C%20Founder%20of%20Popsmith%2C%20lies%20in%20bed%20eating%20popcorn.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a03769a7c7e83f26041ae10%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222143%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETal%20Moore%20is%20the%20cofounder%20of%20Popsmith.%3Cp%3EJason%20LeCras%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETal%20Moore's%20Popsmith%20popper%20made%20Oprah's%20coveted%20%26quot%3BFavorite%20Things%26quot%3B%20list%20in%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20entrepreneur%20said%20the%20product%20hit%20because%20of%20three%20things%3A%20aesthetics%2C%20experience%2C%20and%20flavor.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHis%20advice%20to%20other%20entrepreneurs%20is%20to%20start%20by%20creating%20one%20really%20good%20product%2C%20then%20expand.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPopsmith%20cofounder%20Tal%20Moore%20beat%20the%20odds%20when%20Oprah%20chose%20his%20high-end%20stovetop%20popcorn%20popper%20for%20her%20coveted%20%26quot%3BFavorite%20Things%26quot%3B%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%20said%20an%20Oprah%20Daily%20editor%20told%20him%20the%20team%20reviews%20about%2015%2C000%20products%20a%20year%20before%20Oprah%20makes%20her%20final%20picks.%20In%202024%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpopsmith.com%2Fproducts%2Fthe-popper%3Fvariant%3D42324529348801%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Popsmith%20popper%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20the%20cut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20weeks%20of%20the%20list's%20release%2C%20his%20company%20sold%20out%20of%20every%20popper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20asked%20the%20serial%20entrepreneur%20how%20he%20built%20a%20product%20people%20don't%20just%20buy%2C%20but%20rave%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22793e9c83-6627-48b9-a24e-529b4cc0e2bc%5C%22%3EBorn%20from%20passion%20%E2%80%94%20and%20data%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Popsmith%2C%20Moore%20and%20his%20business%20partner%20ran%20a%20portfolio%20of%20e-commerce%20brands%20that%20sold%20a%20variety%20of%20things%2C%20including%20gumballs%2C%20chocolate%2C%20and%20popcorn%20machines%2C%20but%20only%20one%20category%20really%20held%20their%20interest%3A%20popcorn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20sold%20off%20all%20of%20their%20online%20businesses%20to%20go%20all%20in%20on%20kernels.%20Specifically%2C%20they%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20stovetop%20popper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20had%20proof%20there%20was%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20No.%201%20selling%20popcorn%20popper%20at%20that%20point%20was%20a%20stovetop%20popcorn%20popper%20that%20we%20were%20getting%20from%20another%20supplier%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20thought%2C%20there's%20a%20market%20for%20stovetop%20popcorn%20popping%2C%20but%20a%20more%20elevated%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20premium%20product%20aimed%20at%20the%20kind%20of%20customer%20who%20shops%20at%20Williams%20Sonoma%20or%20Crate%20%26amp%3B%20Barrel%3A%20someone%20who%20loves%20hosting%2C%20cares%20about%20quality%2C%20and%20wants%20durable%2C%20heirloom-style%20cookware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20had%20developed%20something%20like%20that%20in%20popcorn%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20popcorn%20poppers%20in%20the%20market%20are%20very%20carnival%20kitsch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b42ea0db-ce5d-4364-bf5e-8d9e70e90789%5C%22%3EThe%203%20reasons%20his%20product%20hit%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%20said%20the%20Popsmith%20popper's%20appeal%20comes%20down%20to%20three%20things%3A%20aesthetics%2C%20experience%2C%20and%20flavor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20who%20invest%20in%20their%20homes%20care%20deeply%20about%20how%20things%20look%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20world%20shaped%20by%20social%20media%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20flex%20for%20people%20to%20show%20off%20a%20cool%2C%20unique%2C%20innovative%20appliance%20that%20nobody's%20ever%20seen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tal%20Moore%2C%20Founder%20of%20Popsmith%2C%20demonstrates%20their%20product.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0374f695396a3b6e4178a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221071%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Popsmith%20popper%20cooks%20a%20bowl%20of%20popcorn%20in%20under%20five%20minutes.%3Cp%3EJason%20LeCras%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20experience%20aspect.%20As%20he%20puts%20it%2C%20%26quot%3Bnobody%20is%20making%20memories%20in%20a%20microwave.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20stovetop%20popper%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20hear%20the%20popcorn%20popping%20and%20sizzling%2C%20you%20smell%20the%20steam%20coming%20out%2C%20wafting%20through%20your%20kitchen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20see%20it%2C%20you%20taste%20it%2C%20you%20touch%20it%2C%20and%20so%20people%20gather%20around%20in%20the%20kitchen%20and%20have%20this%20shared%20nostalgic%20experience.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20finally%2C%20flavor.%20Moore%20said%20the%20popper%20makes%20authentic%2C%20movie-theater-style%20popcorn%20exceptionally%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221722b723-7683-40cd-ab76-683593d21c40%5C%22%3EHe%20invested%20millions%20of%20dollars%20and%20years%20into%20the%20product%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPopsmith%20was%20expensive%20and%20time-consuming%20to%20build.%20Moore%20said%20it%20took%20two%20years%20to%20develop%20the%20popper%20and%20about%20%243.5%20million%20to%20launch%20the%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20share%20of%20that%20money%20went%20toward%20branding%20and%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20spent%20months%20just%20talking%20through%20and%20really%20understanding%2C%20what%20is%20this%20brand%3F%20Because%20every%20brand%20has%20a%20soul.%20Every%20brand%20has%20an%20identity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20and%20they%20wanted%20Popsmith%20to%20feel%20polished%20and%20distinctive%2C%20from%20day%20one.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20wanted%20to%20go%20to%20market%20looking%20like%20a%20%24100%20million%20brand.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoore%20wouldn't%20necessarily%20recommend%20the%20same%20route%20to%20all%20founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20safer%20approach%20is%20to%20get%20a%20minimum%20viable%20product%20to%20market%20and%20evolve%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20risky%20to%20invest%20so%20much%20time%20and%20money%20before%20launching%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoing-for-growth-how-one-entrepreneur-saved-his-failing-business-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPopsmith%20was%20weeks%20away%20from%20running%20out%20of%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20he%20also%20believes%20their%20decision%20helped%20the%20brand%20land%20major%20retail%20partners%20and%20high-profile%20exposure%20early%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20that%20we%20would%20have%20gotten%20into%20Crate%20%26amp%3B%20Barrel%2C%20Williams%20Sonoma%2C%20Sur%20La%20Table%2C%20and%20Oprah's%20Favorite%20Things%20in%20year%20two%20without%20doing%20all%20that%20preliminary%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220708ed24-92c5-4d6e-a630-d11a3db83c08%5C%22%3EStart%20by%20making%20one%20really%20good%20product%20%E2%80%94%20then%20expand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoore's%20broader%20advice%20for%20entrepreneurs%20is%20to%20start%20by%20creating%20one%20really%20good%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20money%20is%20in%20the%20niche%2C%20and%20you%20want%20to%20stay%20very%2C%20very%20focused%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20direct-to-consumer%20brands%20that%20started%20by%20doing%20one%20thing%20especially%20well%20before%20expanding%3A%20Bonobos%20with%20trousers%2C%20Everlane%20with%20T-shirts%2C%20and%20Harry's%20with%20razors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strategy%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20to%20earn%20trust%20in%20one%20category%20first.%20Once%20customers%20see%20you%20as%20an%20authority%2C%20it%20becomes%20easier%20to%20introduce%20new%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20playbook%20Popsmith%20is%20following%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20earn%20consumers'%20trust%20that%20we%20are%20the%20authority%20in%20the%20popcorn%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20do%20it%20in%20a%20really%20cool%2C%20innovative%20way%20with%20a%20product%20that%20they've%20never%20seen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-create-viral-product-oprahs-favorite-things-list-popsmith-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779270301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0cb653ce0a5b2f12d7d831%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-create-viral-product-oprahs-favorite-things-list-popsmith-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BI'm%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20money%20is%20in%20the%20niche%2C%20and%20you%20want%20to%20stay%20very%2C%20very%20focused%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Popsmith%20cofounder%20Tal%20Moore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kelkins%40businessinsider.com%20(Kathleen%20Elkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%