rday%2C%20you%20might've%20missed%20this%20one%20%E2%80%94%20but%20we%E2%80%99ve%20been%20working%20on%20it%20for%20a%20while%2C%20so%20please%20appreciate%20it%3A%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3Ewe%20strapped%20missiles%20to%20drones.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWe%20now%20have%20drones%20with%20missiles.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20right.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EMissile%20drones.%20%F0%9F%9B%A9%EF%B8%8F%F0%9F%9A%80%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EPew%20pew%2C%20mfs.%20%F0%9F%98%88%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FXu3cNBAnY9%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FXu3cNBAnY9%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20%F0%9F%87%BA%F0%9F%87%A6%20Unmanned%20Systems%20Forces%20(%40usf_army)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fusf_army%2Fstatus%2F2056395215833903335%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMay%2018%2C%202026%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20414%20Magyar's%20Birds%2C%20a%20drone%20unit%20founded%20by%20the%20commander%20of%20the%20USF%2C%20Robert%20Brovdi%2C%20said%20some%20of%20the%20rocket%20strikes%20were%20launched%20at%20%26quot%3Boperational%20depth%20up%20to%20500%20km%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20310%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20about%20the%20distance%20between%20Ukraine's%20border%20and%20Moscow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ukrainians%20said%20that%2C%20besides%20the%20rocket%20strikes%2C%20they%20still%20deployed%20the%20drone's%20original%20132-pound%20explosive%20warhead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ae78d8a-58ce-443d-be85-cb1b1e14334b%5C%22%3EDoubling%20up%20on%20attack%20missions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFitting%20unguided%20rockets%20to%20long-range%20drones%20gives%20Kyiv's%20forces%20an%20expendable%20way%20to%20deploy%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-strikes-hit-russian-factory-black-sea-oil-security-source-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edeep%20in%20enemy%20territory%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20risking%20attack%20helicopters%20or%20strike%20aircraft%20that%20have%20traditionally%20launched%20the%20munitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20rockets%20also%20provide%20a%20more%20cost-effective%20way%20of%20fighting%20at%20such%20a%20range.%20Simpler%20unguided%20rockets%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Ukrainian%20or%20Russian%20S-8%2C%20can%20cost%20a%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20more%20expensive%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-deep-strike-drones-hit-russian-ammo-oil-security-official-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efixed-wing%20drone%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20typically%20priced%20in%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%2C%20could%20use%20the%20cheaper%20rockets%20to%20attack%20secondary%20threats%20while%20reserving%20its%20more%20powerful%20warhead%20for%20a%20primary%2C%20valuable%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tactic%20could%20also%20benefit%20the%20drone's%20original%20mission.%20As%20the%20montage%20suggests%2C%20the%20rockets%20might%20suppress%20or%20destroy%20Russian%20air%20defenses%20seeking%20to%20disrupt%20the%20drone%20mid-flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20launched%20hundreds%20of%20long-range%20drones%20at%20Russia%2C%20but%20many%20are%20brought%20down%20by%20a%20layered%20network%20of%20surface-to-air%20missile%20systems%2C%20electronic%20warfare%2C%20and%20gun%20crews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMagyar's%20Birds%20and%20USF%20didn't%20name%20the%20exact%20drone%20model%20used%2C%20but%20published%20a%20clip%20of%20a%20drone%20shaped%20like%20a%20small%20airplane%20firing%20rockets%20from%20its%20wings.%20The%20video%20emerged%20last%20week%20among%20open-source%20intelligence%20social%20media%20accounts%2C%20which%20said%20the%20drone%20was%20attacking%20a%20Russian%20mobile%20air%20defense%20unit%20in%20Crimea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20could%20not%20independently%20verify%20when%20or%20where%20the%20clip%20was%20filmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drone's%20design%20closely%20resembles%20that%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drones-long-range-moscow-air-defenses-biggest-attack-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EFP-1%20or%20FP-2%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20made%20by%20local%20manufacturer%20Fire%20Point.%20They%20were%20built%20to%20fly%20nearly%201%2C000%20miles%20with%20a%20132-pound%20warhead.%20Each%20is%20reported%20to%20cost%20about%20%2450%2C000%20to%20%2455%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20long-range%20fixed%20wing%20drone%20sits%20on%20a%20factory%20production%20floor.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0a93b894eb4c909fb2d5d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFire%20Point%20builds%20two%20long-range%20drones%2C%20the%20FP-1%20and%20FP-2.%20It%20also%20builds%20a%20long-range%20missile%20called%20the%20Flamingo%2C%20which%20Ukraine%20has%20touted%20as%20one%20of%20its%20main%20weapons%20for%20deep%20strikes%20into%20Russia.%3Cp%3ESerhii%20Okunev%20%2F%20AFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMagyar's%20Birds%20and%20the%201st%20Separate%20Center%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%2C%20too%2C%20has%20deployed%20missiles%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-new-missile-armed-shahed-drone-contains-foreign-parts-ukraine-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erockets%20on%20its%20long-range%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20before.%20In%20December%2C%20Ukraine's%20intelligence%20agency%20said%20the%20Kremlin%20had%20been%20firing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukrainian-interceptor-drone-took-down-russian-shahed-carrying-missile-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ER60%20air-to-air%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20its%20Shahed-type%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20said%20the%20R60s%20were%20used%20against%20Ukrainian%20helicopters%20and%20aircraft%20trying%20to%20destroy%20the%20delta-wing%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20orig