izing%20that%20these%20special%20moments%20we%20had%20together%20at%20lunch%20are%20in%20the%20rear-view%20mirror%20for%20me.%20My%20heart%20aches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225de39376-f119-4ef2-a290-1327532f469e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20lunches%20are%20easy%20to%20set%20up%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20when%20I%20received%20an%20email%20reminder%20via%20the%20school%20newsletter%20about%20parent-student%20lunches%2C%20I'd%20start%20planning%20the%20days%20%E2%80%94%20around%20two%20times%20each%20month%20%E2%80%94%20when%20I%20could%20have%20lunch%20with%20each%20of%20my%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20school%20makes%20it%20fairly%20easy%20to%20go%20in%20for%20a%20lunch%20date.%20All%20I%20had%20to%20do%20was%20check%20in%20at%20the%20front%20desk%20before%20lunch%20begins%2C%20get%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparent-school-volunteering-not-worth-it-parenting-regret-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evisitor%20sticker%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20then%20wait%20for%20my%20child's%20grade%20to%20enter%20the%20cafeteria.%20Once%20the%20kids%20arrive%2C%20I%20could%20sit%20with%20my%20child%20at%20the%20reserved%20tables%20for%20parents%2C%20or%20we%20could%20head%20outside%20to%20the%20tables%2C%20benches%2C%20or%20lawn%20chairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221795%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20poses%20with%20her%20two%20children.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f4b5f09a23d20d291b562a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221346%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20said%20she%20enjoyed%20connecting%20with%20her%20kids%20at%20lunch%20during%20weeks%20that%20they%20were%20with%20their%20father%2C%20whom%20she%20is%20divorced%20from.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Isobella%20Jade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221c2af206-7deb-4545-9b24-ecfec1aa0d08%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20lunches%20meant%20a%20lot%20to%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20lunch%20with%20my%20kids%20was%20never%20just%20lunch.%20As%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-nyc-for-texas-for-husband-now-divorced-stuck-regrets-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enewly%20divorced%20mom%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20having%20lunch%20together%20meant%20so%20much%20to%20me%20as%20I%20adjusted%20to%20splitting%20time%20with%20my%20kids.%20It%20was%20excruciating%20to%20say%20goodbye%20to%20them%20every%20other%20Sunday.%20To%20me%2C%20having%20lunch%20meant%20our%20week%20apart%20could%20include%20some%20extra%20smiles%2C%20laughs%2C%20a%20check-in%2C%20a%20chat%2C%20and%20a%20hug%2C%20all%20in%20the%20span%20of%20a%2036-minute%20lunch%20in%20the%20school%20cafeteria%20or%20in%20the%20green%20area%20outside.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EMy%20divorce%20had%20wrecked%20my%20nervous%20system%20and%20broken%20my%20heart%20to%20pieces%2C%20so%20surprising%20my%20kids%20with%20their%20favorite%20meal%20and%20a%20quick%20hello%20was%20more%20than%20having%20sandwiches%20or%20chicken%20nuggets%20together%20to%20me.%20It%20was%20a%20comfort%2C%20it%20was%20a%20connection%2C%20a%20chance%20to%20look%20into%20their%20eyes.%20I%20know%20my%20kids%20looked%20forward%20to%20these%20brief%20moments%20together%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b5243c43-250c-4888-992d-f6e71b176fe4%5C%22%3EI%20tried%20to%20bring%20their%20favorite%20foods%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20my%20kids%20got%20phones%2C%20I%20would%20often%20surprise%20them%20at%20lunch%2C%20wing%20it%2C%20and%20bring%20whatever%20I%20thought%20they'd%20like%20to%20eat.%20For%20my%20son%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-chick-fil-a-took-over-america-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChick-fil-A%20sandwich%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20no%20pickles%20and%20fries%2C%20and%20Starbucks%20treats.%20Then%20there%20was%20the%20grilled%20cheese%20sandwich%20my%20daughter%20loved%2C%20along%20with%20Whataburger%20chicken%20baskets%2C%20Subway%20sandwiches%2C%20Raising%20Cane's%20chicken%20fingers%20with%20extra%20sauces%2C%20and%20toast.%20Once%20they%20had%20phones%2C%20I%20would%20text%20them%20that%20I%20would%20be%20coming%20the%20next%20day%20for%20lunch%20and%20ask%20them%20what%20meal%20they%20wanted%20me%20to%20bring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author%20poses%20with%20her%20daughter.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69f4b643ab24bc0b23a185fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20poses%20for%20a%20selfie%20on%20a%20sunny%20with%20her%20daughter.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Isobella%20Jade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20our%20lunches%2C%20we%20would%20talk%20about%20what%20was%20coming%20up%2C%20a%20test%2C%20a%20school%20activity%2C%20a%20soccer%20or%20volleyball%20game%20that%20weekend.%20Between%20bites%20of%20a%20salad%20or%20chicken%20wrap%2C%20I'd%20listen%20to%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-conversations-tween-car-rides-to-school-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong%20stories%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20recess%2C%20specials%2C%20and%20their%20lives.%20I%20could%20grasp%20a%20sense%20of%20their%20emotions%20and%20how%20they%20were%20feeling.%20Sometimes%20I%20brought%20Uno%2C%20a%20squishy%20toy%20or%20marker%2C%20and%20a%20coloring%20pad.%20It%20was%20a%20time%20to%20relax%2C%20sit%20back%2C%20and%20just%20chill%20with%20my%20children%2C%20whom%20I%20missed%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d9d08c1-a5bc-494d-8eca-09b25dcd54b2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20wasn't%20easy%2C%20but%20I%20prioritized%20these%20lunches%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20lunch%20took%20some%20coordination%20to%20time%20everything%20correctly%2C%20to%20leave%20my%20work%20projects%2C%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20food%2C%20to%20get%20to%20the%20school%20on%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20my%20kids%20are%20a%20few%20grades%20apart%2C%20I%20would